	<element name="Special (Expanding Strike)" type="Weapon Property" source="Bladetide: Realm of Fauldis" id="ID_NV_FLDS_WEAPON_PROPERTY_SPECIAL_EXPANDING_STRIKE">
		<description>
			<p>Weapons with Expanding Strike property can deal damage when expanded from their folded state.</p>
			<p class="indent"><b>Quarterstaff.</b> You can use bonus action to instantly expand folded quarterstaff to strike your foe. You make an attack against the target, on a hit, target takes 1d6 bludgeoning damage. If you rolled 1 on the attack, you lose grip and drop quarterstaff to the ground.</p>
		</description>
	</element>

	<element name="Special (Compact)" type="Weapon Property" source="Bladetide: Realm of Fauldis" id="ID_NV_FLDS_WEAPON_PROPERTY_SPECIAL_COMPACT">
		<description>
			<p>Weapons with Compact property can fold or reduce their length. You can use bonus action to reduce your weapon into folded state, or to expand it to its full length. Bladed weapons can either hide their blades inside the hilt or separate the blade into different pieces, to save space. Blunt weapons can similarly be reduced, usually via telescopic mechanism. Weapon's weight isn't affected.</p>
		</description>
	</element>

